    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Respite From Newsprint</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by Caroline Groeller responds to May 25 article on reading news on Internet; says article failed to mention the radio as perhaps best alternative to temporarily giving up print newspapers</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The essay about temporarily giving up print newspapers fails to mention perhaps the best alternative: radio. I always feel the most up to date on current events when I have listened to a daily dose of radio news, especially when it comes from National Public Radio.</p>
        <p>CAROLINE GROELLER  Manahawkin, N.J.</p>
      </block>
